    h2 Back Story
    p For this year's IMG T-shirts, I wanted to implement a unique design, something that's out of the ordinary. When I went for my internship in Bangalore, I attended a workshop on Data Visualization. Our instructor, 
      a(href="https://twitter.com/rasagy") Rasagy Sharma 
      | introduced us to data visualisation and how it can be used to make sense out of chaos.
    p One of the projects that he showed us wasÂ 
      a(href="https://github.com/rasagy/viznam") Viznam
      | . In this project, he experimented with names. For each name, he used an algorithm to map it out visually. Each name that was visualised looked similar since they originated from the same algorithm, but their exact geometry differed.

    ul.single
      li.image(style="width:70%")
        img(src="../blog-tshirt-and-data-viz-01.png", alt="Gemnam, a work by Rasagy Sharma")
        span One of his other works in Data visualization. You can check out his 
          a(href="https://agenerativeworld.tumblr.com/") website
          | .

    p I decided to work upon something similar. Hence for our T-Shirt design, I decided to visualise the names of each of our team members on it. In this article, I'll be sharing the experiments that I did in the process.

    h2 Who are we
    p IMG is a group of around 40 tech enthusiasts that manage and maintain the central campus website and the intranet portal of Indian Institute of Technology, Roorkee. We represent the technology front of the campus. We are a bunch of people filled with curiosity and an enthusiasm for building things with technology.
    p I wanted the result to reflect something similar. Hence, initially, I began my experimentation with diagrams that looked like a network of wires. The following section will walk you through my ideas and iterations.

    h2 Experimenting
    h3 Circular network diagrams
    p Initially, I experimented with circular network diagrams and bezier curves. I wanted to use a circular network as a visual representation of a network of wires.

